[{"text": "Liguria Ristorante is your local destination for authentic Italian cuisine in Cape Town.

Whether you're dining in, ordering for takeaway, or hosting a celebration, Liguria Ristorante delivers the true taste of Italy right here in the heart of Cape Town. 
Open for lunch and dinner, family-friendly, amazing bar and selection of wines, and soon we will be opening for breakfast too. 

Located near the Green Market Square. 

Book a table today!

questionsAndAnswers:
[{"question": "Please could you sort out the vagrant problem outside your restaurant. I used to be a
Regular but will not return until you sort out this issue. It has got out of hand and where one used to feel intimidated it  has now become downright  dangerous. ", "answers": [{"answer": "Dear Mike,
The vagrant "problem" is not a Col'Cacchio one to "sort out", but a societal one.

While I agree that feeling intimidated is unacceptable, we need to realize that we live in a very unequal society and world and that until the "vagrants" have a reasonable opportunity and desire "to be somewhere else" it is difficult to eradicate.

Poverty and homelessness is a problem faced by cities across the world. We need to equally empathize with them. 

Equally we need to appreciate that everyone has an equal right to be in public spaces. HOWEVER ONLY when they harass, intimidate or commit crime do they give up that right. 

Please direct your thoughts toward Law Enforcement and Social Development in constructive ways. This is not Col'Cacchio's, the vagrants, the city's, the politician's, your or "other people's" problem. It is ALL our problem. 

While I share you concern for safety, it is unfair to single out the business for this. Please support them. ", "answeredBy": {}}], "askDate": "7 years ago", "askedBy": {}}]

[{"text": "Ala Turkish Returns!

Following the announcement of our revamp in March, we’ve been diligently reimagining the very essence of what makes Ala Turkish unique. From the menu to the interior design, and of course, the desserts (more on those soon), no detail was left untouched.

The journey was long and often challenging, but it was one we embraced wholeheartedly. The warm reception to our grand return made every effort worthwhile.

And this is just the beginning. updatesFromCustomers.text: 菜挺好吃的，但我很反感一点:强制小费。如果你拿单子让我填，我都会写10%及以上。但是你如果强制写上让我再给我不愿意。服务员跟我强调这是他们餐厅的规矩但是我并没有事先得知，并且跟我说如果我不给小费这10%的话需要他们服务人员承担。针对这句话我有个疑问。如果服务员说的是假的那么餐厅培训有问题服务员本人也有问题，如果服务员说的是真的那么餐厅老板的这个行为有问题，客人不愿给的小费需要服务员承担吗？

updatesFromCustomers.text: The service was so good that I almost wanted to propose to our server, but unfortunately, the ambiance was just "meh". The drinks were on point - fast and frosty, just like my ex's heart. As for the food, well, let's just say that I've seen more generous portions in a dieter's lunchbox. The taste was fine, but in my humble opinion, the meat looked a little too gray for my liking. Overall, it was an okay experience - not quite "wow", but not "ow" either

updatesFromCustomers.text:
I always have doubts and am skeptical about how a group of non-Asian could do proper Asian dishes, in particular Chinese ones.
Today, the Kimchi express restaurant has proven me wrong.
The two dishes I ordered today full of the typical Chinese dishes' fragrance. Most importantly, I can sense the 镬气 (also known as "wok hei" where the flavour imparted by cooking food in a wok). Even could easily beats off some of my hometown restaurants!
The staff are friendly and helpful in explaining the options we could add on for those dishes.
I must say, what a hidden gem located in the humble neighbourhood!
Nice wok! 👍👍👍👍👍💯

updatesFromCustomers.text: Great food, good vibes 😍 our Waiter Tadisa made sure we felt like Queens, it was my friends birthday, unfortunately he fell sick during his shift and he had to go home and we were a bit sad, hopefully he’s better now. But thank you so much Tadisa and thanks to Loyiso who then helped after 😍❤️🙌🏾
